  "body": "#### System information\r\nGeth version: v1.8.3-stable-329ac18e/linux-amd64/go1.10\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 16.04.3 LTS\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nAttempting to read token decimal from a valid contract at address \"0x99ea4db9ee77acd40b119bd1dc4e33e1c070b80d\" on specific block number via web3 should not fail.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nInstead, recently the node started to return \r\n`Error: Returned error: missing trie node b03d68ac51042467d7637d4ef9e1c52370abc410f263166965cb1e280b1f6d17 (path )`\r\n\r\n#### Additional information\r\nThe node has been online for 9 weeks without an issue, and just suddenly started failing.\r\nRestarting the node seemed to have pushed back the sync 100k blocks, and the error still persists.\r\n\r\n##### Example web3 call returning an error: \r\n`tokenContract.methods.decimals().call(null, blockNumber)`\r\nwhere blockNumber is the current block number. \r\n##### Example web3 call **not** returning an error: \r\n`tokenContract.methods.decimals().call()`",
